les show the responses to reference stimuli, whereas the arrows show responses to polarized light, with the angle of the symbol denoting the orientation of the E-vector (see Fig. 1). The centre part of the retina, near the fovea, was stimulated; the radiant power was 6 μW for both types of stimuli (2.2×1012 and 1.7×1012 photons per flash, respectively). The latencies following 393 nm flashes are longer than those following stimulation with white light. There is no relationship between the latencies of the oscillatory potentials and the orientation of the E-vector." path-from-xml="JEXBIO_198_2_325F5.tif" /></a><div class="fig-orig original-slide"><a section="17082496" class="fig-view-orig" href="https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/cob/content_public/journal/jeb/198/2/10.1242_jeb.198.2.325/5/jexbio_198_2_325f5.png?Expires=1716296304&amp;Signature=iZmQ2VZx6ycs2dKpHfzq0WsX1egyhavBYXxuPC~FZPJwN7uI2K1Cx4UNwRTsoGV1tuL9AjpuKCn-if-PpMrQwoSiID7~OCMS9T9N-3YmNVq33KS0KmWR~A3XSyfY4b4ifx1w4ONrzks~AQe5Bprrzt1~2~gScOjrXj~-ngTeIyedLgl6UlkFbm~YxHlaD0uE9sj-kLSuj0pbCY~Cb8Pnsib4i9ZckdRN6Lx1lR7nXZBALrE2NTDYPtMeAMZM1ekGwzEapKvZms00bS8NZAhzU7Mnl5p~NcqqAaroFKR4pMU~uqIDRnaqC88gJx8FAttHUJuE-MNxCeZY1GKQyUJDLg__&amp;Key-Pair-Id=APKAIE5G5CRDK6RD3PGA" path-from-xml="JEXBIO_198_2_325F5.tif" target="_blank">View large</a><a section="17082496" href="//cob.silverchair-cdn.com/DownloadFile/DownloadImage.aspx?image=https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/cob/content_public/journal/jeb/198/2/10.1242_jeb.198.2.325/5/jexbio_198_2_325f5.png?Expires=1716296304&Signature=iZmQ2VZx6ycs2dKpHfzq0WsX1egyhavBYXxuPC~FZPJwN7uI2K1Cx4UNwRTsoGV1tuL9AjpuKCn-if-PpMrQwoSiID7~OCMS9T9N-3YmNVq33KS0KmWR~A3XSyfY4b4ifx1w4ONrzks~AQe5Bprrzt1~2~gScOjrXj~-ngTeIyedLgl6UlkFbm~YxHlaD0uE9sj-kLSuj0pbCY~Cb8Pnsib4i9ZckdRN6Lx1lR7nXZBALrE2NTDYPtMeAMZM1ekGwzEapKvZms00bS8NZAhzU7Mnl5p~NcqqAaroFKR4pMU~uqIDRnaqC88gJx8FAttHUJuE-MNxCeZY1GKQyUJDLg__&Key-Pair-Id=APKAIE5G5CRDK6RD3PGA&sec=17082496&ar=7054&xsltPath=~/UI/app/XSLT&imagename=&siteId=1000009" class="download-slide" path-from-xml="JEXBIO_198_2_325F5.tif" target="_blank">Download slide</a></div></div><div class="caption fig-caption"><p>Latencies of oscillatory potentials elicited by flashes (140 ms) of white light (A) and by monochromatic light of 393 nm (B). Filled circles show the responses to reference stimuli, whereas the arrows show responses to polarized light, with the angle of the symbol denoting the orientation of the <strong><em>E</em></strong>-vector (see Fig. 1). The centre part of the retina, near the fovea, was stimulated; the radiant power was 6 <em>μ</em>W for both types of stimuli (2.2×10<sup>12</sup> and 1.7×10<sup>12</sup> photons per flash, respectively). The latencies following 393 nm flashes are longer than those following stimulation with white light. There is no relationship between the latencies of the oscillatory potentials and the orientation of the <strong><em>E</em></strong>-vector.</p></div><a class="close-reveal-modal" href="javascript:;"><i class="icon-general-close"> </i></a></div>
                </div>
                </div>
                <h3 scrollto-destination="17082497" data-legacyid="s3c" id="17082497" data-section-title="Rotating stimuli" class="section-title ">Rotating stimuli</h3>
            <div >
                <div id="17082498" class="article-section-wrapper js-article-section js-content-section  " data-section-parent-id="17082497">
                    
                    <p>We recorded responses to light with a rotating <strong><em>E</em></strong>-vector and to light whose intensity was modulated (with a stationary <strong><em>E</em></strong>-vector). The ERGs and their autocorrelograms evoked by the latter type of stimulus all displayed a marked periodicity. In contrast, autocorrelograms of the responses to polarized rotating stimuli did not contain components with the stimulus frequency (<a reveal-id="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6" href="javascript:;" data-open="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6" class="link link-reveal link-table xref-fig">Fig. 6</a>). This was always so, whether white or coloured stimuli were used and irrespective of the speed of rotation (0.5–4 Hz).</p>
                </div>
                <div id="17082499" class="article-section-wrapper js-article-section js-content-section  " data-section-parent-id="17082497">
                    
                    <a id = "17082499" scrollto-destination="17082499"></a><div data-id="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6" class="fig fig-section"><div class="label fig-label">Fig. 6.</div><div class="graphic-wrap"><a reveal-id="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6" data-open="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6" class="fig-link"><img class="content-image" src="https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/cob/content_public/journal/jeb/198/2/10.1242_jeb.198.2.325/5/m_jexbio_198_2_325f6.png?Expires=1716296304&amp;Signature=NaKVp0EH7j1AqO58vNF4p8mAWDZqpx3n1lk0YQsmGG-V2XE6FoyeUcG39vzu7t4jzmy80PWi4GzMuFNayUcBEcidlrg7aVlmm0TG2wZAr3QycpbQyyJwYu~O0GjaIfimnpkOJhLIG2dVrWOjJp4YTjz0kqIAlMJgJSdY8WavNoYqTK0pjTtS-1qtJkO2GC6x4TupOQCdiX-QWBZZZpO9mdE5th7xdcR5l2DhbxAdoLF69l-h9RgKWsB4m12tZAui45GrqNV~QE0Z78SYyC2sIN8xUxHp0pA4gdLNMHXRd8LyOWT5X9IkXUDb69NTKGn0g4z~VJLrGsnSXZMxAch60w__&amp;Key-Pair-Id=APKAIE5G5CRDK6RD3PGA" data-src="https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/cob/content_public/journal/jeb/198/2/10.1242_jeb.198.2.325/5/m_jexbio_198_2_325f6.png?Expires=1716296304&amp;Signature=NaKVp0EH7j1AqO58vNF4p8mAWDZqpx3n1lk0YQsmGG-V2XE6FoyeUcG39vzu7t4jzmy80PWi4GzMuFNayUcBEcidlrg7aVlmm0TG2wZAr3QycpbQyyJwYu~O0GjaIfimnpkOJhLIG2dVrWOjJp4YTjz0kqIAlMJgJSdY8WavNoYqTK0pjTtS-1qtJkO2GC6x4TupOQCdiX-QWBZZZpO9mdE5th7xdcR5l2DhbxAdoLF69l-h9RgKWsB4m12tZAui45GrqNV~QE0Z78SYyC2sIN8xUxHp0pA4gdLNMHXRd8LyOWT5X9IkXUDb69NTKGn0g4z~VJLrGsnSXZMxAch60w__&amp;Key-Pair-Id=APKAIE5G5CRDK6RD3PGA" alt="(A) Responses to monochromatic light stimuli (494 nm; 4.7×1013 photons s-1) with a rotating E-vector (at a constant intensity level). The ERG following stimulation with the polaroid rotating at 3.9 Hz is plotted as a thin trace and the autocorrelogram of this ERG is plotted as a thick trace. There is no periodicity. The orientation of an E-vector at a given angle θ cannot physically be distinguished from one having an angle θ+180 °, so the frequency of stimulation proper is 7.8 Hz rather than 3.9 Hz. In B, the response to intensity modulation (with a static E-vector) and the autocorellogram are shown: a marked periodicity is present, as would be expected." path-from-xml="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6.tif" /></a><div class="fig-orig original-slide"><a section="17082499" class="fig-view-orig" href="https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/cob/content_public/journal/jeb/198/2/10.1242_jeb.198.2.325/5/jexbio_198_2_325f6.png?Expires=1716296304&amp;Signature=M~5zEuh9NUnu81FxF5lQ0NQdOVUf27uZhPpPwg~4XWoPW6vlvDH1nzMMXrNtL8OE-3KeYyRW2OEXnvLxAgFDj8ZRB6iHXR-jyQsVregz9ndsV1B0oe-gVErjwfOEYh9pWj2CYu3KrZjgqmRhAi65yjiAxBwbVT9EsB-oeo-ZYcm7YcdX~qWax6mw325Ofv~KdaPBYVj9zyxoZa6YWd4un8obO-9nR4p0caQcAU3Yo5VavD2iF9JSBzTaaphdQ424qRuCJeM9cgnrXpEl01WXUh32QAIokelUD-WMXTo3zVj6pjawsoiquVMm~DQVPPgnrGbEblF3XZ6yVeveI4uvWQ__&amp;Key-Pair-Id=APKAIE5G5CRDK6RD3PGA" path-from-xml="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6.tif" target="_blank">View large</a><a section="17082499" href="//cob.silverchair-cdn.com/DownloadFile/DownloadImage.aspx?image=https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/cob/content_public/journal/jeb/198/2/10.1242_jeb.198.2.325/5/jexbio_198_2_325f6.png?Expires=1716296304&Signature=M~5zEuh9NUnu81FxF5lQ0NQdOVUf27uZhPpPwg~4XWoPW6vlvDH1nzMMXrNtL8OE-3KeYyRW2OEXnvLxAgFDj8ZRB6iHXR-jyQsVregz9ndsV1B0oe-gVErjwfOEYh9pWj2CYu3KrZjgqmRhAi65yjiAxBwbVT9EsB-oeo-ZYcm7YcdX~qWax6mw325Ofv~KdaPBYVj9zyxoZa6YWd4un8obO-9nR4p0caQcAU3Yo5VavD2iF9JSBzTaaphdQ424qRuCJeM9cgnrXpEl01WXUh32QAIokelUD-WMXTo3zVj6pjawsoiquVMm~DQVPPgnrGbEblF3XZ6yVeveI4uvWQ__&Key-Pair-Id=APKAIE5G5CRDK6RD3PGA&sec=17082499&ar=7054&xsltPath=~/UI/app/XSLT&imagename=&siteId=1000009" class="download-slide" path-from-xml="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6.tif" target="_blank">Download slide</a></div></div><div class="caption fig-caption"><p>(A) Responses to monochromatic light stimuli (494 nm; 4.7×10<sup>13</sup> photons s<sup>-1</sup>) with a rotating <strong><em>E</em></strong>-vector (at a constant intensity level). The ERG following stimulation with the polaroid rotating at 3.9 Hz is plotted as a thin trace and the autocorrelogram of this ERG is plotted as a thick trace. There is no periodicity. The orientation of an <strong><em>E</em></strong>-vector at a given angle <em>θ</em> cannot physically be distinguished from one having an angle <em>θ</em>+180 °, so the frequency of stimulation proper is 7.8 Hz rather than 3.9 Hz. In B, the response to intensity modulation (with a static <strong><em>E</em></strong>-vector) and the autocorellogram are shown: a marked periodicity is present, as would be expected.</p></div></div><div id="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6" content-id="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6" class="fig fig-modal reveal-modal" data-reveal="data-reveal"><div class="label fig-label">Fig. 6.</div><div class="graphic-wrap"><a reveal-id="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6" data-open="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6" class="fig-link"><img class="content-image" src="https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/cob/content_public/journal/jeb/198/2/10.1242_jeb.198.2.325/5/m_jexbio_198_2_325f6.png?Expires=1716296304&amp;Signature=NaKVp0EH7j1AqO58vNF4p8mAWDZqpx3n1lk0YQsmGG-V2XE6FoyeUcG39vzu7t4jzmy80PWi4GzMuFNayUcBEcidlrg7aVlmm0TG2wZAr3QycpbQyyJwYu~O0GjaIfimnpkOJhLIG2dVrWOjJp4YTjz0kqIAlMJgJSdY8WavNoYqTK0pjTtS-1qtJkO2GC6x4TupOQCdiX-QWBZZZpO9mdE5th7xdcR5l2DhbxAdoLF69l-h9RgKWsB4m12tZAui45GrqNV~QE0Z78SYyC2sIN8xUxHp0pA4gdLNMHXRd8LyOWT5X9IkXUDb69NTKGn0g4z~VJLrGsnSXZMxAch60w__&amp;Key-Pair-Id=APKAIE5G5CRDK6RD3PGA" data-src="https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/cob/content_public/journal/jeb/198/2/10.1242_jeb.198.2.325/5/m_jexbio_198_2_325f6.png?Expires=1716296304&amp;Signature=NaKVp0EH7j1AqO58vNF4p8mAWDZqpx3n1lk0YQsmGG-V2XE6FoyeUcG39vzu7t4jzmy80PWi4GzMuFNayUcBEcidlrg7aVlmm0TG2wZAr3QycpbQyyJwYu~O0GjaIfimnpkOJhLIG2dVrWOjJp4YTjz0kqIAlMJgJSdY8WavNoYqTK0pjTtS-1qtJkO2GC6x4TupOQCdiX-QWBZZZpO9mdE5th7xdcR5l2DhbxAdoLF69l-h9RgKWsB4m12tZAui45GrqNV~QE0Z78SYyC2sIN8xUxHp0pA4gdLNMHXRd8LyOWT5X9IkXUDb69NTKGn0g4z~VJLrGsnSXZMxAch60w__&amp;Key-Pair-Id=APKAIE5G5CRDK6RD3PGA" alt="(A) Responses to monochromatic light stimuli (494 nm; 4.7×1013 photons s-1) with a rotating E-vector (at a constant intensity level). The ERG following stimulation with the polaroid rotating at 3.9 Hz is plotted as a thin trace and the autocorrelogram of this ERG is plotted as a thick trace. There is no periodicity. The orientation of an E-vector at a given angle θ cannot physically be distinguished from one having an angle θ+180 °, so the frequency of stimulation proper is 7.8 Hz rather than 3.9 Hz. In B, the response to intensity modulation (with a static E-vector) and the autocorellogram are shown: a marked periodicity is present, as would be expected." path-from-xml="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6.tif" /></a><div class="fig-orig original-slide"><a section="17082499" class="fig-view-orig" href="https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/cob/content_public/journal/jeb/198/2/10.1242_jeb.198.2.325/5/jexbio_198_2_325f6.png?Expires=1716296304&amp;Signature=M~5zEuh9NUnu81FxF5lQ0NQdOVUf27uZhPpPwg~4XWoPW6vlvDH1nzMMXrNtL8OE-3KeYyRW2OEXnvLxAgFDj8ZRB6iHXR-jyQsVregz9ndsV1B0oe-gVErjwfOEYh9pWj2CYu3KrZjgqmRhAi65yjiAxBwbVT9EsB-oeo-ZYcm7YcdX~qWax6mw325Ofv~KdaPBYVj9zyxoZa6YWd4un8obO-9nR4p0caQcAU3Yo5VavD2iF9JSBzTaaphdQ424qRuCJeM9cgnrXpEl01WXUh32QAIokelUD-WMXTo3zVj6pjawsoiquVMm~DQVPPgnrGbEblF3XZ6yVeveI4uvWQ__&amp;Key-Pair-Id=APKAIE5G5CRDK6RD3PGA" path-from-xml="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6.tif" target="_blank">View large</a><a section="17082499" href="//cob.silverchair-cdn.com/DownloadFile/DownloadImage.aspx?image=https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/cob/content_public/journal/jeb/198/2/10.1242_jeb.198.2.325/5/jexbio_198_2_325f6.png?Expires=1716296304&Signature=M~5zEuh9NUnu81FxF5lQ0NQdOVUf27uZhPpPwg~4XWoPW6vlvDH1nzMMXrNtL8OE-3KeYyRW2OEXnvLxAgFDj8ZRB6iHXR-jyQsVregz9ndsV1B0oe-gVErjwfOEYh9pWj2CYu3KrZjgqmRhAi65yjiAxBwbVT9EsB-oeo-ZYcm7YcdX~qWax6mw325Ofv~KdaPBYVj9zyxoZa6YWd4un8obO-9nR4p0caQcAU3Yo5VavD2iF9JSBzTaaphdQ424qRuCJeM9cgnrXpEl01WXUh32QAIokelUD-WMXTo3zVj6pjawsoiquVMm~DQVPPgnrGbEblF3XZ6yVeveI4uvWQ__&Key-Pair-Id=APKAIE5G5CRDK6RD3PGA&sec=17082499&ar=7054&xsltPath=~/UI/app/XSLT&imagename=&siteId=1000009" class="download-slide" path-from-xml="JEXBIO_198_2_325F6.tif" target="_blank">Download slide</a></div></di